[{"_id":"2b4115a7-48fc-3b18-b395-c7a712e2e7c7","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Stephen, this is some very helpful documentation you have put together hear. Thanks very much for your efforts!","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2011-01-20T19:01:25Z","timestamp":1295550085,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"f369007c-3aa5-3fe3-b23b-e89cf6ae869d","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Fantastic article, really appreciate your work here. It's just a shame I've already encountered most of the pitfalls.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2011-06-19T23:34:43Z","timestamp":1308526483,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"4026f2df-3689-3391-89de-594a1cafb9d6","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Hello,  \r\n\r\nI've been able to program using sockets for a long time but I have never completely understood them. This really demystified everything I had questions about (such as the backlog on a socket's listening function). I'm very excited for my current project as I feel I'll be able to make it better just by reading what you've wrote.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2012-03-02T09:52:04Z","timestamp":1330681924,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"0acccac5-9e74-3107-a15b-b2b1bf93018c","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Very good work!","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2012-06-30T13:11:51Z","timestamp":1341061911,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"ad9a93ef-7cc3-3aed-a280-2b16fe42dc9d","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Excellent work, thank you!","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2013-03-12T20:13:34Z","timestamp":1363119214,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"5dccf232-eb24-3c00-a58b-3886435e19bb","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"If only I read this article a 2 years ago, would have saved me a lot of headaches. Great work!","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2013-04-24T12:27:50Z","timestamp":1366806470,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"73a11b1e-4456-3775-bbf9-25473bc11398","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"This is brilliant! Thank you so much!","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2013-06-14T00:49:55Z","timestamp":1371170995,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"9178e189-a697-3336-8204-a56d54e1e2f8","authorName":"Nathan Peckenpaugh","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Thank you for the invaluable info. Though Im having one minor problem. I'm sending 10 small serialized objects from a server app to a client app (less than 100 bytes each). The Code works great when I step through it in debugger, but when I execute my program at 'full speed' it's not processing all of the objects. Any suggestions on how I can cure this?  ","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2013-11-03T10:28:00Z","timestamp":1383474480,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"7488ca3b-5b19-35b3-a1a5-329ddb6070ea","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"Sounds like your message framing is not working correctly. More than that I can't say without looking at the code.  \r\n\r\nTry to get a minimal repro, post in Stack Overflow, and ping me to take a look at it.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2013-11-04T08:49:00Z","timestamp":1383554940,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"34aaf9a0-3562-3175-a0c2-bddc7baed97a","authorName":"Ben","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"0ecbd2afcc55b93b2b61d467edda6b11","message":"Stephen thank you for writing up this comprehensive guide! Quick question, if I wanted to develop a very simple distributed system (i.e. computing a 'calculation' on 'n' computers'), where robustness is more important than performance, would you suggest using WCF or go with the TcpClient/Socket approach? Time is also fairly limited.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2016-01-25T13:30:14Z","timestamp":1453728614,"authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_gy7FAwf9zz"},{"_id":"4a06587b-9584-3a36-a120-1c359c9cdbd4","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"\"very simple distributed system\" - not sure if that exists. ;)\r\n\r\nI'd say that neither WCF nor plain sockets are best. I'd first recommend using a prebuilt solution, something like Azure HPC or Dryad. If you really do need to write your own, I'd suggest self-hosted SignalR/","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"34aaf9a0-3562-3175-a0c2-bddc7baed97a","date":"2016-01-25T21:02:11Z","timestamp":1453755731,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"},{"_id":"0b2ceb46-db38-386d-b5e9-28eafde8e1bd","authorName":"Senador","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"7947b6ab9482526b6b67e80660fc54dc","message":"Hello Stephen. Thanks for this FAQ. Verifies some of my suspicions. I wonder if you know a solid framework to send strings beetwen two UWP apps. ( Hololens / Tablet ). I looked at SignalR but the Serverpart can't be run on an UWP app yet.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"","date":"2017-02-27T09:42:37Z","timestamp":1488188557,"authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_UVLgRebpHy"},{"_id":"29e1e28d-2a8a-36e2-a175-5a081797afba","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"Nope, sorry.","postId":"2009_04_tcpip-net-sockets-faq-9b093540-8aac-3007-8be7-c8f2db2ee2bc","replyTo":"0b2ceb46-db38-386d-b5e9-28eafde8e1bd","date":"2017-02-27T15:16:26Z","timestamp":1488208586,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}]